verseObjects.content: + \ft The proper names \fqa Joseph and Mary \fqa* were not in the original text, and are supplied for the reader from the third person plural verb.
+ \ft Some ancient copies add to the text the name of his father, \fqa Joseph \fqa* ;  and some do not have the mention of the mother. The most reliable copies have \fqa his father and mother \fqa* .
+ \ft Some scholars translate "about my Father's business" as \fqa in my Father's house \fqa .
